1 Download Fedora Server Iso
2 Flash It Using Fedora Media Writer
3 Setup Fedora Server
4 Update The System using sudo dnf update -y if its too long dont update it
5 Install Gnome Using sudo dnf install gnome-session
6 Enable GDM3 sudo dnf install gdm -y
sudo systemctl enable gdm --force
7 Switch to Graphical Target sudo systemctl set-default graphical.target
8 sudo reboot
9 If Theres No Terminal Go to tty3 using ctrl alt f3 then login then use sudo dnf install gnome-terminal -y
  After You Install gnome terminal then exit tty3 using command exit then go back to tty2 using ctrl alt f2
10 Install fastfetch using sudo dnf install fastfetch
11 Install Nano If Its Not Installed sudo dnf install nano
12 Enable Submenu Using Change GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU=true to GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU=false
13 Enable Recovery Change GRUB_DISABLE_RECOVERY="true" to GRUB_DISABLE_RECOVERY="false"
14 Disable BLSCFG Using GRUB_ENABLE_BLSCFG=true to GRUB_ENABLE_BLSCFG=false
15 Update Grub Using sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg
  For UEFI Systems sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/efi/EFI/fedora/grub.cfg
16 Enable Custom Font by Opening 3 bars button then Preferences Then Profiles Unnamed Or Your name Then Enable Custom Font
17 Install Gnome Apps (If Needed)
-For Core GNOME Applications Use sudo dnf install nautilus gedit gnome-system-monitor gnome-control-center -y
-For Useful GNOME Utilities sudo dnf install gnome-tweaks gnome-calculator gnome-disk-utility gnome-screenshot -y
-For Extra GNOME Apps sudo dnf install gnome-weather gnome-maps gnome-clocks gnome-contacts gnome-photos -y
18 Install Firefox Using sudo dnf install firefox -y
19 Download Trinity Logo From Readme https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Trinity-Linux Then Save The Trinity Logo As Then Rename 537255355-6369081e-a3f4-4ecf-ab9d-4eca552a8936.png To trinity-logo.png
20 Install Background Using sudo dnf install gnome-backgrounds -y
21 For other Photo apps use sudo dnf install eog -y
22 Move Trinity Logo Using sudo mv /home/yourname/Pictures/trinity-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps
23 Change OS Release sudo nano /etc/os-release
   Then Change Name Fedora Linux To Trinity Linux then Change 43 (Server Edition) To Workstation Then Change Pretty name fedora to Trinity
   Then Change All Name on /etc/os-release from fedora to trinity id and etc Change Home URL fedoraproject.org to https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Trinity-Linux
24 Change all any fedora logo such as fedora-gdm-logo.png and fedora-logo.png using sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/trinity-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/fedora-gdm-logo.png then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/trinity-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/fedora-logo.png
   then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/trinity-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/fedora-logo.ico then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/trinity-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/fedora_logo_med.png then sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/trinity-logo.png /usr/share/pixmaps/fedora_logo_small.png
25 Change GRUB so it shows Trinity instead of Fedora, youâ€™ll need to edit the GRUB configuration
   sudo nano /etc/default/grub Then Change GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="$(sed 's, release .*$,,g' /etc/system-release)" To GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR="Trinity"
   Then Update Grub Using sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/grub2/grub.cfg
   For Uefi Systems sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/efi/EFI/fedora/grub.cfg
26 Install Gnome Software Using sudo dnf install gnome-software -y
27 Install Libreoffice (If You Need It) use sudo dnf install libreoffice -y
28 Install Gnome Extension (If You Need It) sudo dnf install gnome-extensions-app -y

29 Have Fun And Start Using Trinity Linux Which Is Have 28 Steps And You can Say I USE TRINITY BTW
                                     
